On 3/19/2010 7:59 PM, Michael Rule wrote:
> Hi Mike,
>
>   I always thought the Type4 engine was well-balanced. What do you
> s'pose caused the increased vibration as the heads were kicking off?

Cylinder compression was out of balance.  One of the heads had failing 
valve seats and that was making the engine run really poorly.  Ended up 
breaking exhaust parts, cracked alternator bracket, wore holes in the 
fan housing, etc..
